&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Kard is transforming customer loyalty with our rewards-as-a-service API platform. We empower our partners, from neobanks to financial institutions and beyond, to offer tailored rewards that celebrate customers&#39; daily transactions. Backed by $30M from industry-leading investors and seasoned experts, we are reshaping the future of customer engagement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kard&#39;s data team has built a strong measurement foundation and automated much of the repeatable work. Now we need someone senior enough to own what can&#39;t be automated: the high-stakes customer conversations where nuance, credibility, and judgment determine outcomes. As Measurement Lead, you’ll be the person our sales and account team turns to when a merchant has questions about their campaign results, when an issuer needs to understand impression attribution, or when the data doesn’t tell a clear story.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on senior role. You&#39;ll write SQL, dig into dashboards, and investigate data questions directly — because we&#39;ve built the data org around automation and engineering, not manual analyst headcount, and this work calls for someone with the judgment to match. Reporting to the CTO, you&#39;ll sit at the intersection of Data Science, Analytics Engineering, Product, and GTM, and you&#39;ll carry the field&#39;s voice back to the teams building our measurement products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret lift measurement test results quickly, and codify internal understanding by educating and consulting GTM stakeholders on the results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own high-priority measurement conversations with merchant and issuer partners, translating complex results into clear, credible external narratives tailored to the audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as GTM&#39;s trusted advisor on ambiguous, data-intensive customer questions, engaging engaging clearly and credibly with our sophisticated and highly analytical marketing clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write SQL and work directly in data to investigate performance, validate hypotheses, and support customer and GTM needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build dashboards, visualizations, and lightweight reporting tools that help GTM and customers successfully pull and interpret results directly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Data Science to refine Kard&#39;s measurement approach, including experimentation design, incrementality methodology, and reporting frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep fluency in Kard&#39;s reporting, product behavior, and business model so you can answer questions with sound judgment — not scripts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify patterns in recurring measurement questions and improve workflows, tooling, and handoffs between GTM and the data org.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface reporting and tooling gaps to Product and Engineering, representing what the field actually needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Desired Skills&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–8 years in measurement, analytics, consulting, or partner-facing data roles — ideally in adtech, martech, fintech, or marketplaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong fluency in measurement concepts: experimentation, incrementality, attribution, and a clear-eyed view of what different methods can and cannot say.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid SQL skills and comfort working directly in BI tools to build or manipulate dashboards and visualizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent judgment in ambiguous situations — you think on your feet and respond calmly to hard questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate complex analytical ideas clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences, including analytically sophisticated external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
